    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-26T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-26T13:00:00-05:00" n="430"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d430">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.90H/38: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Straus</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-26T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 26, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>438. Your 905, October 18, noon. Quoted text for Article 4 is satisfactory to the
                    Department.</p>
                <p>In view of previous doubts about Afghan position regarding most-favored-nation
                    treatment, you should assure yourself that the Government of Afghanistan
                    understands the language to carry the obligation of unlimited and unconditional
                    most-favored-nation treatment. This should be confirmed by a statement in
                    writing from the Afghan Minister to you. The statement need not be considered a
                    formal part of the agreement or published with it. This having been
                    accomplished, you may proceed to signature.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
